This is an excerpt from the Cherokee Supreme Court docket for the years 1823 to 1834. The Cherokee Supreme Court convened annually in New Echota beginning on the second Monday in October and lasting three weeks. This excerpt is from the Monday October 17, 1825 session of court, in which several cases were heard. Entries from this Supreme Court docket cover items ch100-ch163.

body.value: Monday 17th Court convened agreeable to adjournment Present their Honors John Martin &C et cetera Jurors George Saunders Foreman, Daniel Griffin , Thos Thomas Saunders , The Chip , Suttowaka Johnson Fields Ptf Plaintiff vs Nathan Hicks Dft Defendant a plea of debt Judgement in favor of the plaintiff, with costs of 22 cents Oocoosee Ptf vs Crying Wolf Dft a plea of trespass It is the opinion of the Court that the defendant shall keep the contended man George Saunders Fore Foreman Benjamin Timpson Ptf vs Chowanka his old wife Dft Continued
